#
# ### Wave MC2-swarm (2026-04-18 MC2 + H06 attack-and-heal, AP741-AP742)
#
# Two scope-discipline anti-patterns surfaced in the 2026-04-18
# MC2 + H06 audit. Companion to the Wave-14 MC5 ambient-discipline
# patterns (AP296, AP261).
#
# **AP741 (Pro-object-limit-vs-chain-level ambient drift in MC
# status-table).** Status-table row reads "all-degree convergence
# PROVED" without naming the ambient category. For a class-M chiral
# algebra, $\Theta_\cA$ exists in $\pro\text{-}Ch(\Vect)$ (pro-object
# over the weight filtration), NOT in $Ch(\Vect)$ on the nose; the MC
# equation holds in the completed dg-Lie algebra $\widehat{\gAmod}$,
# not in $\gAmod$. Bare "all-degree convergence" invites confusion with
# chain-level existence of the positive-genus MC element as a genuine
# chain complex, which is FALSE for class M (infinite support, no
# termination) and only TRUE for class G/L/C. Counter: every convergence
# status claim must name the ambient category and the limit mechanism
# (inverse limit, filtered colimit, bar-length completion).
# Distinct from AP296 (weight-preservation fallacy on bar differentials
# where OPE simple-pole summands strictly drop weight): AP296 catches
# a specific bigrading error; AP741 catches the broader practice of
# stating chain-level results without ambient-category qualification.
# Related: AP261 (single-index ML vs bigraded ML — correct arity of
# grading), AP258 (cohomological-vs-chain status drift — correct level
# of resolution). AP741 is the ambient-category sibling.
#
# **AP742 (Alt-proof SKETCHED mislabelled as "conditional").** The
# "Alternative Proofs Secured" block lists H06 (KS scattering) as
# "conditional on support-property comparison (open)". "Conditional"
# invites treating H06 as a proof waiting on a single missing input.
# Source reality is a REMARK with a PROOF SKETCH and TWO uninscribed
# packages: (a) central-charge map construction (free variable, no
# canonicalisation); (b) KS support-property comparison (Kontsevich-
# Soibelman 2008, Def. 1 + Remark 1). Counter: for every "Alternative
# Proofs Secured" entry, distinguish INSCRIBED / SKETCHED / CONJECTURAL
# / PROPOSED; audit all eleven H-rows. Distinct from AP280 (three-step
# epistemic inflation remark → standalone → headline): AP742 is
# inflation-within-status-table from "sketch in a remark" to
# "conditional alt-proof" in a single banner. Related: AP255
# (phantom-file), AP305 (pessimistic drift — AP742 is the
# optimistic-drift sibling at the alt-proof layer).
