#
# \begin{remark}[Ambient category of $\Theta_\cA$]
# \label{rem:mc2-ambient-category}
# \index{Maurer--Cartan element!ambient category}
# For the reader tracking the ambient-category semantics of the
# all-degree MC element: $\Theta_\cA \in \MC(\widehat{\gAmod})$, where
# $\widehat{\gAmod} = \varprojlim_N \gAmod / F^{N+1}$ is the
# weight-filtration completion
# \textup{(}Definition~\textup{\ref{def:weight-filtration-tower}}\textup{)}.
# As a pro-object in $\pro\text{-}Ch(\Vect)$ this limit is well-defined
# and complete Hausdorff
# \textup{(}Theorem~\textup{\ref{thm:recursive-existence}}(iv)\textup{)}.
# As a chain complex in $Ch(\Vect)$ on the nose, $\Theta_\cA$ has finite
# chain-level presentation only for classes $\mathbf{G}$, $\mathbf{L}$,
# $\mathbf{C}$ \textup{(}depth $d_{\mathrm{alg}} \in \{0,1,2\}$;
# termination at degrees $2$, $3$, $4$ respectively\textup{)}; for class
# $\mathbf{M}$ the support is unbounded and $\Theta_\cA$ is genuinely a
# pro-object. This distinction is the ambient-category analogue of the
# one-channel vs multi-channel distinction in
# Remark~\ref{rem:mc2-bar-intrinsic-perspective}: scalar saturation
# controls PARAMETRIZATION by $\kappa$; ambient-category semantics
# controls EXISTENCE in $Ch$ vs $\pro\text{-}Ch$. The weight filtration
# indexed by $w(g,r,d) = 2g - 2 + r + d$ is OPERADIC (stability exponent
# of stable graphs), distinct from the conformal weight grading on bar
# words where the bar differential's simple-pole summands strictly drop
# weight; Mittag-Leffler on the operadic filtration is unconditional and
# lives in its strongest form (surjective transitions), while
# Mittag-Leffler on the conformal-weight grading of bar words would fail
# (and correctly is not invoked at any step of the proof).
# \end{remark}
